messages.message:
Patch Set 18: Code-Review-1

(44 comments)

(defect) You have some on stack char buffers that you pass to snprintf(). It looks like this:

 char buf[AMIR_BUF_LEN];
 ...
 snprintf(buf, AMIR_BUF_LEN, ...);

It's supposed to look like:

 char buf[AMIR_BUF_LEN];
 ...
 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), ...);

It's much easier to verify the correctness on the second form during review.

(defect) Similarly you have lots of:

 node = calloc(1, sizeof(struct ll_amir));

Which should be:

 node = calloc(1, sizeof(*node));

For the same reason as above.

(style) Please add cy_ prefixes to cYAML structure member names...

(style) No need for extern on function prototypes.

(style) When you have to break a binary operation over two lines then the operator is supposed to go at the end of the first line.

(style) You have lots of unnecessary parens around comparisons. This is a readability fail since it looks like you're trying to suppress the "suggest parentheses around assignment used as truth value" compiler warning. I'm so used to that warning that extra parens seem to suggest to me that it is an assignment. Other Lustre developers have commented similarly.
